Definition: the freezing of a seriously ill or recently deceased person to stop tissues from decomposing
Example: the body is preserved until new medical cures are developed that might bring the person back to life; cryonics is more science fiction than serious science
Synonyms: adj, pert, cryonic, cryobiology, the, freezing, of, a, seriously, ill, or, recently, deceased, person, to, stop, tissues, from, decomposing, body, is, preserved, until, new, medical, cures, are, developed, that, might, bring, back, life, more, science, fiction, than, serious
Category: noun.cognition
